Top-shelf vegan food! We will definitely be going again. We stopped by this place on a quiet Wednesday night around 6:30.  Appetizer: the Texas Queso, which turned out to be a seven-layer dip thing with some amazing vegan cheese and sour cream. Served with great chips that I think must be house-made.  Entrees: the Classic burrito, with the grilled seitan added. This is the burrito of your dairy-free dreams! The seitan is cooked to perfection and packed with flavor, the cheese is great, and the rest of the burrito is a perfect blend of rice, black beans, corn, guac, salsa, sour cream, and (I think) a bit of mole sauce. These are a lot of food - my partner couldn't quite finish theirs after the Queso starter. This is one of the best vegan burritos I've eaten anywhere and I can't recommend it highly enough.  Dessert: Pear Three Ways. This was delightful, especially the donut. We found the dark chocolate ice cream a bit too authoritative, so that the entire dish just ended up tasting like rich chocolate ice cream - hardly a problem, but it did obscure some of the more subtle pear flavors. Still, delicious.  Service: Fast and correct. We didn't ever feel like we were waiting, either for our server or for our food. Nothing negative at all to say here.  Ambience: My partner described it as "1970s but self-assured about it" and I think that's pretty accurate. You can definitely tell it's a nightclub even when the dance floor's not open. Still, it was quiet enough that we were able to have an intimate conversation without difficulty.

It’s impossible to overstate how bad my experience at Black Flamingo was—which is even crazier considering the wait staff were nice and apologetic, and the food which I ended up receiving was pretty good.  I placed a takeout order for four at the (then-empty) bar at 6:38. It came out at 7:50. Needless to say waiting over one hour for a takeout order is unacceptable.  During this time an entire round of dinner service turned over, including multiple takeout orders placed after mine. I was surprised and hungry.  The takeout order that *did* arrive was missing more than one item. (And a minor point, but it also was missing plasticware and napkins.)  Not being one to belabor or relive a bad experience, I called them to see what could be done about my missing items.  I spent *fifteen minutes* on the phone—mostly on hold—with the disaffected managerial staff who eventually agreed to refund me... for just the food I paid for but didn’t receive. I’ll need to wait two business days for those charges to clear, apparently.  Strangely, they asked what they could do to make the situation right, to which I suggested comping maybe *one* of the four entree orders for my time.  The make-good I was offered was one free cocktail, later *that same night*, which (needless to say) would require me to take the time and effort to revisit the establishment I want nothing to do with and I was already far away from.  I’m honestly shocked that what should have been an easy solution to a (hopefully) one-off SNAFU was handled so poorly. Sadly for this vegetarian, I’ll never visit Black Flamingo again.
